-- Singapore Stocks: Creative Tech, Neptune Orient, STATS ChipPAC
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 2012-02-01T09:42:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/singapore-stocks-creative-tech-neptune-orient-stats-chippac.html
Singapore ’s  Straits Times Index (FSSTI)  lost
0.1 percent to 2,904.76 at the close. About the same number of
stocks rose and fell in the 30-member gauge.  The following were among the most active shares in the
market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.  CDL Hospitality Trusts (CDREIT)  , the operator of hotels
in Singapore,  Australia  and  New Zealand , fell 2.8 percent to
S$1.725. Citigroup Group Inc. cut its rating to “sell” from
“neutral,” citing slowing tourist arrivals.  Creative Technology Ltd. (CREAF)  (CREAF SP) slipped 2.9 percent to
S$2.32 after the maker of digital music players said its net
loss widened to $33.9 million in the second-quarter ended Dec.
31 from a $10.9 million a year earlier.  Neptune Orient Lines Ltd. (NOL)  (NOL SP),  Southeast Asia ’s
biggest container carrier, climbed 5 percent to S$1.365,
tracking gains among the region’s biggest shipping companies on
speculation rising cargo rates will boost earnings.  SIA Engineering Co. (SIE)  , the aircraft maintenance unit
of Singappore Airlines Ltd. (SIA SP), advanced 2 percent to
S$3.54. The company said third-quarter profit rose 5.3 percent
from a year earlier to S$63.5 million.  STATS ChipPAC Ltd. (STAT)  , a provider of chip-testing
and packaging services, dropped 2.9 percent to 51 Singapore
cents after posting a fourth-quarter loss of $46 million,
compared with a gain of $19 million a year earlier. The company
said it booked $55.5 million in impairment charges from flood
damage to its facility in  Thailand .  To contact the reporter on this story:
